If the system does not have make tool

Use this to compile the source:
	
	Make a directory ./build
	mkdir -p ./build

	Compile the code into that directory
	javac -d ./build ./src/com/pionix/*.java

Use this to if you want to re-build javadoc:
	
	Make a directory ./docs
	mkdir -p ./build

	Build java doc into that directory
	javadoc -d ./docs ./src/com/pionix/*.java

To run the project

	java -cp ./build com.pionix.Main

To clean the project

	rm -rf ./build